description.plain:
Andrew Bazzi is a self-made American-Lebanese singer who found his start on the now-canceled video social media platform, Vine. On the platform, he collaborated frequently with user, Rajiv Dhall, who also discovered a vast following on YouTube once the platform collapsed.

Bazzi grew up in Canton, Michigan where he learned how to play the guitar at a very young age. Before beginning his solo career, Bazzi wrote and produced numerous songs for a myriad of K-Pop artists, including EXO and TAEYEON.

His first-ever single, “Mine,” topped the iTunes charts and debuted on the Billboard Top 100 at No. 56 in February 2018, peaking at No. 11. Later that year, Bazzi released his debut album, COSMIC, and joined Camila Cabello and Justin Timberlake on tour.

2019 saw Bazzi release his debut mixtape Soul Searching, which peaked at twenty on the Billboard 200. Weeks after the album’s release, Bazzi began work on his second full-length LP.

songs.title: Mine

description.plain:
Bazzi’s fifth single, “Mine,” describes his love interest, where Bazzi confesses his obsession with the girl.

The single topped the iTunes Charts and preceded his sixth single, “Why.” While his previous single, “Beautiful,” didn’t do terribly, “Mine” reached over 2 million downloads on Spotify in less than two months, and debuted on the Billboard Hot 100 at No. 56, peaking at No. 11.

Although the song released in October 2017, the song picked up massive traction in January 2018. Most of this can be attributed to a Snapchat Lense (example) and viral internet meme (below) which featured the song.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ELy6RQfj2gM

songs.title: Beautiful

description.plain:
“Beautiful” is Bazzi’s fourth single and predecessor to his iTunes topping, “Mine”. Focusing on theme of love and desire, Bazzi is aware that life is short so as a result, he wants to let his lover know that their beauty and imperfections are truly adored.

The ballad was first teased on his Twitter, where it’s unknown whether Bazzi was purposely fishing for retweets or if the song was actually never intended for release like he described.

https://twitter.com/bazzi/status/880533548842733569

songs.title: Beautiful (Remix)

description.plain:
This remix of Bazzi’s “Beautiful” adds pop singer, Camila Cabello to the mix. The original song was released on July 13, 2017—around a year before the two would embark on Camila’s Never Be The Same Tour together. The exhibition kickstarted on April 9, 2018, and featured Bazzi as the opening act.

Bazzi and Camila both posted a picture of the song artwork on their respective Instagram and Twitter accounts, teasing the track and release date.
